reviewText: This is a sad attempt at story telling and I think destroys the Magoo character. I'm okay with revamping things from time to time for series but there's no original hear here.

As a baby boomer, I was looking forward to enjoying the Mr. Magoo cartoon(s) from the 60's and 70's however, this video was from a later cartoon version of moreso the 90's era. I chose this video because it was free for Prime Members.  The 'real' classics of Mr. Magoo episodes (now in videos) could only be viewed for a price because in my opinion, they are the most desired by people of all ages -- just like most of the classic Westerns' videos can only be viewed for a price.  I closed the video out at the very beginning because I was disappointed that it was not one of the classics.  Why can't wholesome classic Westerns and Cartoons be free, especially for Prime Members.
I love Mr magoo, my 7 year grandson really enjoyed the movie. I wish there were more movies for children like this one.

Eight year-old LOVED it!  ... and Dad found it pretty hilarious in a throw-back way also!  Regardless, a very nice, simple yet good, funny story with lots of laughs. My son immediately wanted to search for more Magoo movies on Amazon and watch more!!  That's about as good of a compliment as you can get :)

I am very disappointed in this cheaply produced Magoo film!  Somehow it just doesn't elicit the same kind of belly laughs as in yesteryear.  This Magoo is not as funny or comedic as before and falls flat in my humble opinion!  The artwork and animation is not nearly as good as the ones produced for Movie Theatres years ago!

I grew up with watching the original Mr. Magoo and this movie didn't remind me of that! I understand that this is a new day and age, but some things you can leave the same and people will still watch it ;-) If it isn't broke, don't try fixing it...lol
